 <p><CENTER><A HREF="http://ak.lonelygamer.com">
<IMG SRC="http://www.plattsflello.com/ryn.gif" BORDER=0></A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukhamelleon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Khamelleon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 94<br> <font color=#E9D756>(2/8/02 7:18:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2999.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogues - gotta love em :P</span><hr size=1> As a nearly exclusive player of ROgues, I pickpocket until I max out my skill, because I need the skill both for my Burning Rapier (which I plan to do again, though I'm twinked enough not to ever need it) and my epic.  However, I was responsible enough to max the skill as soon as I got it.  Now I only need to use PP for five skill points every time I level, until it hits 200.  That doesn't translate into much PPing.  No one seems to care, because since I only pp every third (if im in a group of three), fourth (if im in a group of four, etc.) mob and don't look the others unless im in one of those groups that doesn't seem to ever loot and the corpses start to pile up.  Or unless I'm in a group with one of those people who decides to take it upon himself to rightclick so fast on every corpse that I just start to get annoyed and loot something just so he or she can't have EVERYTHING (LoL if you play alternates you've seen these people).  <br>
<br>
The ONLY other time I pped was when I was grouped with me, enchanter, and druid and they asked me to taunt the mobs before breaking the mes.  Backstab by itself wasn't cutting it, so I'd pp the monster twice and then backstab, which usually was enough to draw aggro.  They didn't seem to mind, as it was Orcs in Highpass and they were twinks they didn't care much about the few GP i looted anyway.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uluviahoodyhooo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Luvia Hoodyhooo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 154<br> <font color=#E9D756>(2/8/02 9:18:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2999.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogues - gotta love em :P</span><hr size=1> I've often wondered why they haven't implemented a &quot;Soandso has stolen Xplat/Xitem from Xmob&quot; message for when someone pickpockets in group.  Sure, yeah yeah it's a role playing game and PP shouldn't be noticed if it's successful etc etc.  But the fact of the matter is that PPing from your group's mobs without prior notification is not cool.   I'd even say it borders on anti-social behaviour, although not as bad as most other anti-social acts.<br>
<br>
<br>
-Luvia <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukhamelleon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Khamelleon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 95<br> <font color=#E9D756>(2/8/02 9:25:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2999.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogues - gotta love em :P</span><hr size=1> I don't know how well you relate to your characters, but as a Rogue veteran, something in my mind says that my rogue really doesn't care if his PPing is antisocial.  If he did, he would have been a Paladin.<br>
<br>
Even if you don't roleplay at all, isn't there SOME part of your class that just ingrains itself into your personality while playing?  Whether your a troll, or a Rogue...  heck I've seen nonroleplaying Vah Shir purring for fun.<br>
<br>
/shrug <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uassonacetherake.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Assonace The Rake</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#E9D756>(2/8/02 9:42:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2999.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogues - gotta love em :P</span><hr size=1> Pickpocket is an Important Skill for a Rogue considering you have to have it very high to get ur epic to tell you the truth i would look down on a rogue who doesnt sure if i pick a Blue Diamond or Some valuable gem im gonna pipe up and say something but if i steal a ruby or something liek taht sure ill keep it.....More power to pickpocketers That something you have to deal with when you group with one to get our mad Skillz <p><HTML><BODY>
