Feather Silverthorn Thief  E marr <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ustarborncometchaser.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Starborn Cometchaser</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 92<br> <font color=#E9D756>(2/8/02 10:08:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2999.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogues - gotta love em :P</span><hr size=1> Here is a question for the people who are mad at rogues for doing this.  Do you get mad at your clerics for not sharing any plat they get for rezzing while in your group?  Both are class abilities, but I would imagine the rogue ability is &quot;stealing from group&quot;.<br>
<br>
Not that I particularly care one way or the other on either of these topics just curious if this is a class discussion or character(of player) discussion. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uleldariluthiniel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Leldari Luthiniel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 132<br> <font color=#E9D756>(2/8/02 10:12:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2999.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogues - gotta love em :P</span><hr size=1> I was in LoIO when Meblo got booted from his group for pickpocketing. It got very heated in OOC so I can only guess what tells were like. I group with rogues a lot. If we are just exp grouping by all means pick-pocket and split at the end. On item camps keep those fingers in your own pocket. That said I don't know who is right or wrong here....wasn't in the group. I was solo'ing the chancellor to get prods for guildies. But the OOC did get pretty angry and things may have been said not meant by either side. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ustarborncometchaser.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Starborn Cometchaser</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 94<br> <font color=#E9D756>(2/8/02 10:18:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2999.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogues - gotta love em :P</span><hr size=1> BTW for people who will start up on rogues picking the &quot;good shit&quot;<br>
<br>
You can't PP &quot;MAGIC&quot; items, mainly the most stuff, gems, spells, coin. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/bemarr.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=yalladar>Yalladar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#E9D756>(2/8/02 10:27:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2999.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Roleplaying Rogues</span><hr size=1> I wonder how this impacts rogues everywhere.  If I'm hunting HG's for instance in RM, do I want a rogue in my group?  Maybe not.  Could I trust him/her not to pp?  It might be good roleplay to not care about whether your group cares about you pp, but do you think it impacts your chances and the chances of rogues everywhere to find a group.  My rogue friend frequently has problems finding a group, could distrust be part of it?  Being a ranger, I have a little difficulty finding groups, but not nearly as much trouble as my IG friend does.<br>
<br>
Someone mentioned being in a group that doesn't loot, WTF is with that?  I'd rather have someone right clicking faster than everyone else in the group than have nobody looting.  I hate grouping in DL, but when I do, nobody loots.  Makes it difficult to target incoming mobs when there's loads of corpses in the way.  Even though I don't really need or sometimes even want the pp off the mobs there, I do my fair share of corpse cleanup.  I've been in groups where I've constantly have to remind people to loot.  I know the /assist key can target the puller's target but only when he's close enough.  I frequently (If I'm not pulling) like to run out and meet the mob early so i can backpedal and shoot a few arrows before it comes to the group.  It's hard to see where the puller is coming from when corpses are in the way.  I don't to clean em all up, cause I don't want to look like I'm looting everything.<br>
<br>
